        "excerpt": "   Sometimes, users would like to focus on only one task and its subtasks on Quire, especially when they have a long task list and want to hide all the other tasks from the screen. This is when the “drill down” (zoom in) feature comes in handy.   Simply follow these steps:   1. Select a task in your project, and press Z to zoom in on it          2. Then, you will only see the task and its subtasks          To further zoom in on a subtask, press the Down arrow key to select it and then press Z.   To zoom out, press A.     See you in our next post!  ",
